				   <h3>CPD Code for Registrants </h3>
					<p>Continuing Professional Development (CPD)is an essential aspect that the  Engineering Technicians, Incorporated Engineers and Chartered Engineers Should take care of and facilitate throughout their professional career. In particular they should: </p>
					<ul class="list10">
					<li><i class="fas fa-caret-right" aria-hidden="true"></i>Appropriate plan for the meeting of the learning and development needs, which should be framed after discussion with the employer and taking ownership of the plan. 
					<li><i class="fas fa-caret-right" aria-hidden="true"></i>Following the opportunities of development and simultaneously following the plan of development and undertaking a variety of developmental activities.
					<li><i class="fas fa-caret-right" aria-hidden="true"></i>Recording of the CPD activities that they undertake
					<li><i class="fas fa-caret-right" aria-hidden="true"></i>Undertaking reflective activities concerning the CDP program and recording these reflections for future reference.
					<li><i class="fas fa-caret-right" aria-hidden="true"></i>Evaluation of the CPD activities against the benchmarked objectives and keeping a recor of this as well.
					<li><i class="fas fa-caret-right" aria-hidden="true"></i>Review their learning and development plan regularly following reflection and assessment of future needs.
					<li><i class="fas fa-caret-right" aria-hidden="true"></i>Mentoring others and sharing professional expertise and knowledge to ensure better support in learning and development of other members.
					</ul>
